text:
TAL SCULLY; Experimental
physics is cool.

J-Lab has a very wide
range of experiments

So my partner and I, we did
a biophysics experiment,

we did a spectroscopy
experiment, which

is like physical
chemistry, and then

we did an experiment
with cosmic ray muons.

So we covered a
wide range of ways

to apply physics
to the real world.

And it was really neat to see
that range and interact with it

and analyze data for lots of
different fields of physics.
